I'd say that doing 3 pset classes is less of the problem here, more so you definitely want to do 70 before 170 imo, not concurrently. You'll have a lot harder time in 170 without the background built up in 70. 70 and 16B together is chill though, especially if you did well in 16a.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

I highly recommend taking 70 before 170. The proof technique is extremely important for 170.

children.subject: 16B is also (technically) a prereq for CS70.
Is 70 a prereq for 170? If not then you're good taking them together but if it is a prereq, they started manually enforcing prereqs for 170 this Fall so you might not get in.

I would advise against semesters like these if your not in a rush. Even if your are a giga chad brainiac, if your early in your undergrad then there are plenty of other courses that you might wanna take that would relieve you instead. There is really no need for added stress, and the time constraint is the same for everyone--if you want to get the most out of your courses, then its best to adequately plan them (likewise for the rest of your undergrad courses). 

Also I would def recommend 70 before 170 if you havent really been exposed to that sort of material before--it make things much easier for you.
